            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                Integrating technology into teaching can enhance student engagement, provide diverse learning experiences,
                and facilitate a deeper understanding of complex concepts. This section showcases examples of how technology
                can be used to create interactive and effective learning environments.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Sample 1: Gorillas Game AI Explanation</h2>
            <p>
                This example explains the AI behind the classic "Gorillas" game, implemented using JavaScript in Visual
                Studio Code. It demonstrates how rule-based AI can be used to simulate game logic and create engaging
                interactive experiences.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="example1.html">View Example 1: Gorillas Game AI</a>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Sample 2: Proton NMR Spectroscopy Visualizer</h2>
            <p>
                This example allows students to visualize molecules and their corresponding proton NMR spectra.  This
                interactive tool, also developed in JavaScript, provides a dynamic way to explore the relationship between
                molecular structure and spectroscopic data.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="example2.html">View Example 2: Proton NMR Visualizer</a>
            </p>
